---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Template Changelog"
  description="Every QuantumSOP template change, documented: what changed, why, and whether you need to update. Transparency first."
  docId="QSOP-WEB-005"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Version Control · Public Record</p>
      <h1>Template Changelog</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Every change to QuantumSOP documents is recorded here with the reasoning, the
        triggering source, and customer guidance. You should never wonder "why did this
        change?" or "do I need to update?"
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="changelog-entry">
        <p class="meta">v1.0 · 02 JUL 2026 · INITIAL PUBLICATION</p>
        <h3>Readiness Kit v1.0 published</h3>
        <p>
          Initial release of the seven core artifacts, four strategic guides, and
          onboarding materials. Reviewed against current NIST, OMB, and CISA guidance
          as of the review date stamped on each document.
        </p>
        <p><em>Customer action: none — this is the baseline release.</em></p>
      </div>

      <p class="note">
        Monitoring cadence: FAR changes, NIST standards, CISA guidance, OMB memoranda,
        and RFP language patterns are reviewed on a weekly-to-quarterly schedule.
        Proposed rules and opinion pieces do not trigger updates — final, authoritative
        sources do.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
